This paper deals with energy efficiency in wireless networks, specifically in the context of multi-node cooperative systems. The paper proposes a joint spectrum and power allocation scheme, which involves resource allocation and UE-BS association. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on wireless networks and resource allocation, cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely sub-categories.
